    "The country's strategy involves not only setting standards for AI safety and security but also addressing broader concerns such as privacy, equity, civil rights, consumer and worker protection, and competition.",
    "This holistic approach aims to secure the benefits of AI while mitigating potential risks [119].",
    "The involvement of industry leaders in shaping these regulations is a critical aspect of the U.S. strategy.",
    "By inviting key players in the AI industry to participate in congressional hearings, the U.S. government is ensuring that the regulatory framework is informed by those at the forefront of AI development.",
    "This collaboration facilitates a more nuanced and effective regulatory environment, one that supports new inventions while providing necessary oversight [2]."
